01:11.680 --> 01:16.599
My name is Laura Benson. I live
at 19 Hazel Grove, Kingsbere.

01:16.600 --> 01:19.919
Why have you come
to the station today, Laura?

01:19.920 --> 01:23.158
I read about the woman who was raped.

01:23.159 --> 01:26.800
It happened to me too.
I was raped.

01:26.839 --> 01:28.479
And when was this?

01:29.839 --> 01:33.359
Two years ago... almost.

01:33.360 --> 01:35.799
June 2. It was a Saturday.

01:35.800 --> 01:38.719
Do you know who the person was
that did this to you?

01:38.720 --> 01:41.478
No. I still don't.

01:41.479 --> 01:44.119
And where... where did the attack happen?

01:45.560 --> 01:50.679
I was walking home from the pub,
the Rising Sun in Abbots Chapel.

01:50.680 --> 01:55.639
Been a big do, place was packed.
They had music, late lock-in.

01:57.839 --> 02:00.359
The last of us left
around half three.

02:00.360 --> 02:04.559
And when you left the pub, did
you leave alone, or with others?

02:04.560 --> 02:06.359
Alone.

02:06.360 --> 02:09.239
What happened when you left the pub?

02:15.720 --> 02:17.158
I wasn't far from home.

02:17.159 --> 02:18.878
There's a field you cross diagonally -

02:18.879 --> 02:20.478
it's just long grass, never got mowed -

02:20.479 --> 02:22.560
takes you into the back of Kingsbere.

02:26.039 --> 02:27.958
I was right in the middle of it

02:27.959 --> 02:30.038
when I thought I heard something.

02:30.039 --> 02:32.359
I was about to look
behind me, I dunno why,

02:32.360 --> 02:35.638
I could just sense
someone running at me.

02:35.639 --> 02:37.679
I think he punched me.

02:37.680 --> 02:40.279
I got hit from behind.

02:40.280 --> 02:42.519
Just knocked me right out.

02:43.879 --> 02:45.879
Do you have any idea how long

02:45.920 --> 02:48.279
you were knocked out
before you came round?

02:48.280 --> 02:50.039
No.

02:52.000 --> 02:55.118
When I came round, there was
something in my mouth.

02:55.119 --> 02:58.479
It was like thick
material, gagging me.

03:00.280 --> 03:04.000
My hands were tied behind
my back and he was on top of me.

03:04.959 --> 03:06.799
He smelt of drink.

03:06.800 --> 03:08.638
What sort of drink?

03:08.639 --> 03:14.039
Spirits. I don't know why
I remember that. Cheap spirits.

03:14.079 --> 03:16.719
Are you able to describe him to us?

03:16.720 --> 03:19.958
I-I don't know. I couldn't
see him. I'm sorry.

03:19.959 --> 03:22.119
It's alright, you're doing really well.

03:25.720 --> 03:29.919
What did you do with your
clothes from that night, Laura?

03:29.920 --> 03:33.279
I washed them.
Never wore them again.

03:33.280 --> 03:35.280
Have you still got them?

03:37.600 --> 03:41.479
And did you speak to anyone
about the attack at the time?

03:43.000 --> 03:45.679
My GP. A week or two after.

03:45.680 --> 03:49.280
She told me I should report it.
I told her I didn't want to.

03:50.839 --> 03:54.720
I didn't tell anyone... till now.

03:56.360 --> 03:58.878
Why didn't you want
to report this at the time?

03:58.879 --> 04:01.199
I know what happens.
I read the papers.

04:01.200 --> 04:05.199
I'd had a lot to drink.
I mean, a lot.

04:05.200 --> 04:08.199
Plus, short skirt, nice top, make-up.

04:08.200 --> 04:10.400
You think I don't know
what they'd do to me?

04:11.839 --> 04:13.878
I know how women like me get treated.

04:13.879 --> 04:15.639
Not by us.

04:17.360 --> 04:20.600
What made you change your mind today?

04:22.519 --> 04:27.279
I read it in the papers and I
was sick in the toilets at work.

04:27.280 --> 04:29.680
I just thought, "What if it's him?"

04:31.720 --> 04:34.638
"What if it's the same man?"

04:34.639 --> 04:39.438
"I didn't report it, and
he's done it to someone else."

04:39.439 --> 04:44.400
"I could've stopped it...
if I'd been braver."

04:46.400 --> 04:50.039
"I know what she's going
through and it's my fault."

05:19.360 --> 05:20.919
Thank you.

05:20.920 --> 05:22.318
You were very brave

05:22.319 --> 05:24.158
coming to see us today, Laura.

05:24.159 --> 05:27.039
I don't know how you've kept it
to yourself for so long.

05:27.079 --> 05:28.919
You're doing the right thing now.

05:28.920 --> 05:30.478
I want you to know,

05:30.479 --> 05:32.279
it doesn't matter
how long ago this was.

05:32.280 --> 05:34.078
We'll investigate this as thoroughly

05:34.079 --> 05:35.838
and robustly as we can.

05:35.839 --> 05:37.518
We'll do everything we can

05:37.519 --> 05:39.920
to find the person
that did this to you.

05:39.959 --> 05:43.199
We'll keep you fully up-to-date
with what happens now, OK?

05:43.200 --> 05:47.038
But you will need support.
Have you got anyone to talk to?

05:47.039 --> 05:49.400
I got married six weeks ago.

05:51.439 --> 05:53.679
He doesn't know.

05:53.680 --> 05:56.159
Do I tell him?

06:02.360 --> 06:04.279
There's no way
she could have known

06:04.280 --> 06:06.279
the details of what happened to Trish.

06:06.280 --> 06:10.038
No, we haven't released them and
Trish has told nobody but us.

06:10.039 --> 06:13.078
Which means this could
be the same attacker.

06:13.079 --> 06:16.159
And Trish isn't his first victim.

06:19.920 --> 06:21.518
She didn't report it 'cause she thought

06:21.519 --> 06:23.599
she wouldn't be treated
with respect or dignity.

06:23.600 --> 06:26.600
Well, then we prove to her
that she will and we catch him

06:26.639 --> 06:30.200
and we make sure he goes away
for a very, very long time.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.079
Is that him?

06:41.439 --> 06:43.359
Yeah, looks like it.

06:43.360 --> 06:46.359
Oh, Mum, I'm not sure
why you agreed to this.

06:46.360 --> 06:48.638
He asked.

06:48.639 --> 06:50.158
Can you be sure that

06:50.159 --> 06:52.238
it definitely wasn't him
who attacked you?

06:52.239 --> 06:53.919
We're just talking.

06:53.920 --> 06:56.238
You don't have to do anything,
unless there's any trouble.

06:56.239 --> 06:58.600
But if you think
there might be trouble...

07:19.839 --> 07:22.518
What was that, security?

07:22.519 --> 07:24.519
Just looking out for me.

07:27.159 --> 07:30.360
Does she know? About us?

07:31.519 --> 07:33.639
She'll be figuring something's up.

07:43.360 --> 07:47.999
It weren't me, Trish.
I didn't do it.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.319
You know that, don't you?

07:52.519 --> 07:56.679
Well, you must know that.
I mean, well, why would I?

07:56.680 --> 07:58.759
What?

08:01.920 --> 08:03.599
Police came to see me.

08:03.600 --> 08:07.400
They know about us,
about Saturday morning.

08:07.439 --> 08:09.078
Yeah.

08:09.079 --> 08:12.039
Bloody hell, Trish. This is
some kind of mess now, innit?

08:13.839 --> 08:16.919
I just think Cath doesn't need to know.

08:16.920 --> 08:19.838
Right. That's what you think, is it?

08:19.839 --> 08:22.679
Well, what good's it gonna do?

08:22.680 --> 08:24.559
We owe her the truth.

08:24.560 --> 08:27.238
Do we? Really?
How's that gonna help?

08:27.239 --> 08:29.359
I'll tell her it was a mistake.

08:29.360 --> 08:32.438
Oh, great. Like that's gonna
make all the difference.

08:34.280 --> 08:38.198
You tell her, I'm gonna
have to pack my bags.

08:38.200 --> 08:41.799
- Might not be like that.
- Course it bloody will.

08:41.799 --> 08:45.519
She's gonna find out, Jim.
It might as well be from me.

08:52.280 --> 08:55.680
You have no idea what
you're letting yourself in for.

09:07.519 --> 09:09.199
So Aaron Mayford...

09:09.200 --> 09:12.478
- How was the surveillance?
- Yeah, uh, it was fine.

09:12.479 --> 09:14.200
Doesn't look like it from your face.

09:14.239 --> 09:16.478
Alright, not fine -
Steve was off getting food,

09:16.479 --> 09:18.318
and Mayford got in the car with me.

09:18.319 --> 09:20.478
- What?!
- Look, the point is...

09:20.479 --> 09:22.919
I think we found something
in his work history.

09:22.920 --> 09:24.599
Go on.

09:24.600 --> 09:26.999
So the company that Mayford
worked for as an IT consultant

09:27.000 --> 09:28.878
had contracts with Flintcombe Farm Shop

09:28.879 --> 09:30.438
and Coopers Telemarketing,
which is where

09:30.439 --> 09:32.958
this new woman, Laura Benson, works.

09:32.959 --> 09:35.159
He has a connection with both women.

09:37.479 --> 09:39.479
Let me do this one.

09:47.159 --> 09:48.838
- Yeah?
- Hi, Aaron.

09:48.839 --> 09:51.359
We'd like you to come to the
station, answer some questions.

09:51.360 --> 09:53.559
- Who is it? Who is it?
- Get back inside.

09:53.560 --> 09:55.239
- What for?
- Back!

09:58.879 --> 10:00.719
I don't wanna come.

10:00.720 --> 10:02.999
Aaron Mayford, I'm arresting you

10:03.000 --> 10:05.118
in connection with
an incident of sexual assault

10:05.119 --> 10:07.279
on 28 May in the Axehampton area.

10:07.280 --> 10:10.279
You do not have to say anything,
but it may harm your defence

10:10.280 --> 10:12.038
if you do not mention when questioned

10:12.039 --> 10:13.759
something you later rely on in court.

10:13.800 --> 10:17.360
Anything you do say may be given
in evidence. Understand?

10:18.600 --> 10:20.000
Yeah.

10:39.639 --> 10:42.199
Bit lazy, though, isn't it?

10:42.200 --> 10:47.599
You know, woman gets raped,
you pull in the local rapist,

10:47.600 --> 10:50.758
even if you don't know
the full facts of his story.

10:50.759 --> 10:53.719
We need blood, urine,
pubic hair and penile swabs too.

10:53.720 --> 10:55.279
We'll need your written consent.

10:55.280 --> 10:57.638
And if I don't give you my consent?

10:57.639 --> 10:59.199
Any future jury could take

10:59.200 --> 11:01.280
a negative inference if you refuse.

11:03.119 --> 11:04.999
Aaron, can you clarify for us

11:05.000 --> 11:07.158
where you were this past Saturday night,

11:07.159 --> 11:11.118
between approximately 10pm and 5am.

11:11.119 --> 11:13.078
I was fishing.

11:13.079 --> 11:15.279
- Where were you fishing?
- Off the beach.

11:15.280 --> 11:18.200
- Which beach?
- The one next to the sea.

11:19.759 --> 11:23.238
Between the caravan park
and the cafe at Bartons End.

11:23.239 --> 11:25.878
Were you anywhere near
Axehampton on Saturday night?

11:25.879 --> 11:27.999
- No.
- Or the party

11:28.000 --> 11:29.999
that was going on at Axehampton House?

11:30.000 --> 11:31.679
As I wasn't in Axehampton,

11:31.680 --> 11:33.878
I wouldn't have been
near the house, would I?

11:33.879 --> 11:37.199
You drove
your own car to go fishing?

11:37.200 --> 11:40.078
- Yep.
- What route did you take?

11:40.079 --> 11:42.518
Same as usual -
out on the St Andrews Road,

11:42.519 --> 11:45.399
onto the coast road,
down to the car park.

11:45.400 --> 11:47.599
- Same on the way back?
- Same on the way back.

11:47.600 --> 11:50.158
- Well, that makes sense.
- Glad you're happy.

11:50.159 --> 11:53.158
Except you didn't.

11:53.159 --> 11:55.638
Either way.

11:55.639 --> 11:57.599
We've checked the CCTV.

11:57.600 --> 11:59.679
Your car didn't go that
route in either direction,

11:59.680 --> 12:04.038
any time between Saturday
afternoon and Sunday afternoon.

12:04.039 --> 12:06.679
You must've missed me.

12:06.680 --> 12:09.000
We're pretty thorough.

12:10.319 --> 12:12.078
You said there were other men

12:12.079 --> 12:13.799
fishing off the beach on Saturday.

12:13.800 --> 12:15.518
- What were their names?
- No idea.

12:15.519 --> 12:17.238
Don't you ever talk to them?

12:17.239 --> 12:19.799
I don't go to the
beach at night to talk.

12:19.800 --> 12:21.318
I go to be alone.

12:21.319 --> 12:23.359
- You like being alone, Aaron?
- Yeah.

12:23.360 --> 12:25.799
- Find people annoying?
- No.

12:25.800 --> 12:29.199
- I find this annoying.
- Right.

12:29.200 --> 12:31.518
What about this is annoying to you?

12:31.519 --> 12:34.359
Being victimised again for something

12:34.360 --> 12:36.758
I didn't even do in the first place.

12:36.759 --> 12:38.999
What did you catch?

12:39.000 --> 12:40.599
What?

12:40.600 --> 12:43.279
- What fish did you catch?
- Mackerel.

12:43.280 --> 12:47.158
- How many?
- Dozen or so.

12:47.159 --> 12:50.238
It's not difficult.
You could probably do it.

12:50.239 --> 12:52.518
- What did you do with them?
- What?

12:52.519 --> 12:55.559
What did you do with the
mackerel after you caught them?

12:55.560 --> 12:57.878
Put it in the cooler.

12:57.879 --> 12:59.919
Brought it home
at the end of the night.

12:59.920 --> 13:04.720
- What did you do with them then?
- I ate them, the next day.

13:06.039 --> 13:08.238
- Who cooks them?
- Me.

13:08.239 --> 13:10.038
You ate all of them the next day?

13:10.039 --> 13:12.958
There were a dozen.
So we had about six or seven.

13:12.959 --> 13:14.838
What did you do with the others?

13:14.839 --> 13:17.038
Froze them. Why, do you want a couple?

13:17.039 --> 13:18.919
No.

13:18.920 --> 13:21.799
So if we were to go to your house now,

13:21.800 --> 13:23.958
your wife would confirm and back up

13:23.959 --> 13:26.199
that you cooked her
fresh mackerel on Sunday?

13:26.200 --> 13:27.559
Yep.

13:27.560 --> 13:29.719
And if we were to look in your freezer,

13:29.720 --> 13:32.360
we'd find the remainder
of the mackerel in there?

13:33.920 --> 13:36.639
That's if she hasn't been
at them while I've been here.

13:39.800 --> 13:41.638
Have you ever been to Abbots Chapel?

13:41.639 --> 13:45.799
- Oh, she speaks.
- Answer the question, please.

13:45.800 --> 13:47.599
Dunno.

13:47.600 --> 13:51.319
- Do you know the village I mean?
- Yes.

13:52.680 --> 13:55.518
Do you know
the Rising Sun pub there?

13:55.519 --> 13:57.399
I don't think so.

13:57.400 --> 14:00.720
- Never been in there?
- Should I have?

14:00.759 --> 14:04.359
- It's a yes/no question.
- No.

14:04.360 --> 14:07.118
What about Kingsbere?
You ever been to Kingsbere?

14:07.119 --> 14:09.799
Are you just gonna run through
a list of local places?

14:09.800 --> 14:11.679
Answer the question, Aaron, please.

14:11.680 --> 14:13.438
Have you ever been to Kingsbere?

14:13.439 --> 14:16.159
- Yes.
- When?

14:18.079 --> 14:20.039
I had a mate who lived there.

14:20.079 --> 14:22.478
We played football
together a few times.

14:22.479 --> 14:24.000
Name?

14:25.560 --> 14:27.518
Dave King.

14:27.519 --> 14:30.518
- Does he still live there?
- Dunno. We fell out of touch.

14:30.519 --> 14:33.078
It's amazing what happens
when you go to prison.

14:33.079 --> 14:35.360
Your social life falls apart.

14:38.159 --> 14:41.078
Wait, Abbots Chapel is, um...

14:41.079 --> 14:42.958
Abbots Chapel is the next
village over, right?

14:42.959 --> 14:45.038
Well, we used to drink in a pub there.

14:45.039 --> 14:48.199
So if that's the Rising Sun, then, yes.

14:48.200 --> 14:51.359
But not recently?

14:51.360 --> 14:52.758
No.

14:52.759 --> 14:56.919
- Few years back?
- Yeah.

14:56.920 --> 15:01.318
- 2013? 2014?
- Bit before, probably.

15:01.319 --> 15:04.118
Ever been to Flintcombe Farm Shop?

15:04.119 --> 15:07.158
Yes. I used to do the IT support.

15:07.159 --> 15:10.038
The company I worked
for had the contract.

15:10.039 --> 15:12.559
- Who'd you deal with there?
- The owner.

15:12.560 --> 15:16.238
Um... What was his name? Ed?

15:16.239 --> 15:18.399
Meet any of the other staff there?

15:18.400 --> 15:21.199
No.

15:21.200 --> 15:24.438
And you did some work for
Coopers Telemarketing?

15:24.439 --> 15:28.638
Yeah. Yeah, their system
was a right old mess.

15:28.639 --> 15:32.639
And was it Laura Benson
in charge of their IT contract?

15:35.039 --> 15:40.119
No. It was a bloke. Terry somebody.

15:40.159 --> 15:42.359
You didn't have anything
to do with Laura Benson?

15:42.360 --> 15:45.319
I've never met Laura Benson.

15:52.360 --> 15:55.038
Do you want the bacon
in the fridge or the freezer?

15:55.039 --> 15:56.638
'Cause there's quite a lot of it.

15:56.639 --> 15:58.478
You really didn't have to do all this.

15:58.479 --> 16:00.399
It's not me, is it? It's Ed.

16:00.400 --> 16:03.238
He wouldn't let me come here
without half the shop.

16:03.239 --> 16:06.559
I just find it quite hard
that everyone seems to know now.

16:06.560 --> 16:08.158
Hey, nobody's judging you.

16:08.159 --> 16:10.439
Why would they be judging me?

16:11.920 --> 16:14.399
Well, no, that's what I'm saying.
They're not judging you.

16:14.400 --> 16:16.319
You know, we're all here for you.

16:19.560 --> 16:21.759
Cath, I-I need to
talk to you about something.

16:23.239 --> 16:26.158
About the attack?
Is it about what he did to you?

16:26.159 --> 16:28.078
Because you know
you can tell me anything.

16:28.079 --> 16:29.799
I'm not gonna tell anyone, I promise.

16:29.800 --> 16:31.439
- I'm your mate so...
- No.

16:34.600 --> 16:37.360
Me and Jim, we had sex.

16:38.920 --> 16:41.319
Saturday morning.

16:43.400 --> 16:45.119
What?

16:48.600 --> 16:50.518
No.

16:50.519 --> 16:52.318
Trish...

16:52.319 --> 16:55.279
We did and I'm sorry,
and it shouldn't have happened.

16:55.280 --> 16:58.199
- If I could take it back, I...
- Wait, wait. Just shut up.

16:58.200 --> 17:01.079
Just shut up. Shut up, Trish.
Just... just stop talking now.

17:06.638 --> 17:08.400
It was you?

17:12.200 --> 17:15.199
Yeah, you see, I-I, um...

17:15.200 --> 17:17.518
I thought there was someone
on Saturday morning,

17:17.519 --> 17:19.358
and I gave myself
a talking-to, you know,

17:19.359 --> 17:22.238
"Not on the day of your party.
Give the man a break."

17:22.239 --> 17:23.560
But you?

17:25.759 --> 17:27.319
Really?!

17:28.600 --> 17:29.600
You?

17:33.159 --> 17:35.280
Christ, his standards have slipped.

17:39.439 --> 17:41.238
So, um...

17:41.239 --> 17:44.038
- Was it here, was it?
- Yeah.

17:44.039 --> 17:46.158
Jesus.

17:46.159 --> 17:48.719
I never knew the smell
of mildew turned him on.

17:48.720 --> 17:50.438
I'm sorry.

17:50.439 --> 17:53.238
Why did you do it then
if you're so bloody sorry?

17:53.239 --> 17:55.719
He'd come round
to look at the boiler.

17:55.720 --> 17:58.199
Well, he certainly
did that, didn't he?

17:58.200 --> 18:00.118
- It wasn't planned.
- No, no.

18:00.119 --> 18:02.238
It's never planned with Jim, never is.

18:02.239 --> 18:04.638
But he's always ready
when called upon.

18:04.639 --> 18:07.158
I mean, you know you're
not the first, don't you?

